description:
A new volume of Samurai Jack that picks up where the cult animated series left off after it was cancelled in its fourth season by Cartoon Network. The comic, written by Jim Zub and illustrated by Andy Suriano, was originally planned as a five-issue mini-series. IDW Publishing doubled their commitment to a minimum of ten issues shortly after strong sales of the first issue and positive response from fans, in the end the series lasted a total of twenty issues.

In February 2013, IDW had reached an agreement with Cartoon Network to return and bring many characters from classic Cartoon Network shows to comics.

Collected Editions

  • Samurai Jack: The Threads of Time (#1-5)
  • Samurai Jack: Tales of the Wandering Warrior (#1-20)
  • Samurai Jack: The Scotsman's Curse (#6-10)
  • Samurai Jack: The Quest of the Broken Blade (#11-15)
  • Samurai Jack: The Warrior-King (#16-20)
name: Samurai Jack

description: One day while visiting his grandparent’s farm outside Shiraoi, Japan, The young Japanese American Tetsu Yushi came across a strange cabin and an unfinished samurai sword with a dark hidden secret curse. Once he accidentally is stabbed by the blade he enters a blood pact with the Yuki-Onna Maiyuki and is tasked with finding a way to free himself and Mai of the curse the blade holds. A journey that will transverse the world and encounter strange and dangerous encounters of with demons, spirits, ghosts and many more creatures of legend. Hoping that one day the two of them will be free of the blades curse.
